abstract_summ: Records were reviewed of 85 patients with COVID-19 between February 4 and 16, 2020 . Primary outcome was in-hospital mortality at 28 days . Baseline leukocyte count, neutrophil count and hemoglobin were significantly higher in non-survivors compared with survivors . The reverse was true of lymphocyte count and platelet platelet, PaO2/FiO2, CD3+ count and CD4+ count .
